    +improveDocsLink
    h1 Menu Vue Component
    ul.docs-index
    p Menu component not so often seen in mobile apps. But it is proven to be extremely helpful when you need controls on top of the map, images, some text/code editor, etc.
    p Menu Vue component represents <a href="../docs/menu.html">Menu</a> component.
    h2 Menu Components
    p There are following components included:
    ul
      li `f7-menu`
      li `f7-menu-item`
      li `f7-menu-dropdown`
      li `f7-menu-dropdown-item`
    h2 Menu Properties
    table.params-table
      thead
        tr
          th Prop
          th Type
          th Default
          th Description
      tbody
        tr
          th(colspan="4") &lt;f7-menu-item&gt; properties
        tr
          td text
          td string
          td
          td Menu item text
        tr
          td icon-only
          td boolean
          td
          td Enable if menu item contains only icon
        tr
          td dropdown
          td boolean
          td
          td Enable if menu item contains menu dropdown
        tr
          td link
          td boolean
          td
          td Enable if to render menu item as link (`<a>`) element if you don't need to specific `href`
        tr
          th(colspan="4") &lt;f7-menu-item&gt; icon related properties
        +vueLinkIconProps
        tr
          th(colspan="4") &lt;f7-menu-item&gt; navigation/router related properties
        +vueLinkRouterProps
        tr
          th(colspan="4") &lt;f7-menu-item&gt; action related properties
        +vueLinkActionsProps

        tr
          th(colspan="4") &lt;f7-menu-dropdown&gt; properties
        tr
          td content-height
          td string
          td
          td CSS value of dropdown `height` property. Specify only to limit dropdown height if there are a lot of items
        tr
          td position
          td string
          td
          td Dropdown position, can be `left`, `center` or `right`
        tr
          td left
          td boolean
          td
          td Same as #[position="left"]
        tr
          td center
          td boolean
          td
          td Same as #[position="center"]
        tr
          td right
          td boolean
          td
          td Same as #[position="right"]
        tr
          th(colspan="4") &lt;f7-menu-dropdown-item&gt; properties
        tr
          td text
          td string
          td
          td Menu dropdown item text
        tr
          td divider
          td boolean
          td
          td Render this item as divider (text will ignored in this case)
        tr
          td link
          td boolean
          td
          td Enable if to render menu item as link (`<a>`) element if you don't need to specific `href`
        tr
          th(colspan="4") &lt;f7-menu-dropdown-item&gt; navigation/router related properties
        +vueLinkRouterProps
        tr
          th(colspan="4") &lt;f7-menu-dropdown-item&gt; action related properties
        +vueLinkActionsProps


    h2 Menu Events
    table.events-table
      thead
        tr
          th Event
          th Description
      tbody
        tr
          th(colspan="2") &lt;f7-menu-item&gt; events
        tr
          td click
          td Event will be triggered on menu item click
        tr
          td menu:opened
          td Event will be triggered right after menu dropdown will be opened
        tr
          td menu:closed
          td Event will be triggered right after menu dropdown will be closed
        tr
          th(colspan="2") &lt;f7-menu-dropdown-item&gt; events
        tr
          td click
          td Event will be triggered on menu dropdown item click

